  <description type="morphology">Plants rigid, somewhat glossy. Stems 3–7 cm, branches to 10 mm, spreading. Stem leaves 2.3–3 × 0.8–1 mm; base abruptly rounded to insertion; marginal teeth partly recurved; costa 90–100% leaf length; alar cells 6–10 × 7–11 µm, region opaque, ± clearly delimited, extending almost to margins; laminal cells 35–65 × 5 µm, walls moderately porose; basal juxtacostal cells 9–11 µm wide, more distal juxtacostal cells elongate, in 2–4 rows, walls strongly pitted; cells in acumen rhombic. Sporophytes unknown in North America.</description>
